How to run ae_splp.cpp:

1) Download the source file ae_splp.cpp 

2) Open Terminal

3) Navigate to the folder with the cpp files (for dropbox, you can just run the following command - without quotes - "cd ~/Dropbox/SCARF\ RA\ 2016/Yunus/ae_splp_Cpp”)

4) Now you can run and compile running "g++ ae_splp.cpp && ./a.out 1000 1000”

——— How to run Letchford's tests: —— 

You need to change two things to run different test cases. “./a.out 1000 1000”

First argument specifies the number of facilities and clients
Second argument specifies the denominator of the fixed cost (10 refers to large fixed costs etc.)